ically downloads and installs packages from AUR, a full list can be found <a href=\"https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/AUR_helpers\">here</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T09:48:38.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bradleythughes/blackbox\">Blackbox</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bradleythughes/blackbox\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">29</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":29,\"repo\":\"bradleythughes/blackbox\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Lightweight window manager for the X window system, without library dependencies. Built using C++.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-03-21T17:31:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.yoctoproject.org/software-item/matchbox/\">Matchbox</a> - Environment for X running on non-desktop embedded platforms such as handhelds, set-top boxes, kiosks and anything else for which screen space, input mechanisms or system resources are limited.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-03-19T18:26:25.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://unauthorised.org/dhog/9wm.html\">9wm</a> - Window manager that attempts to emulate the Plan 9 window manager 8-1/2 as far as possible within the constraints imposed by X.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://dwm.suckless.org/\">dwm</a> - Dynamic window manager for X. It manages windows in tiled, monocle and floating layouts. All of the layouts can be applied dynamically, optimising the environment for the application and task performed.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.enlightenment.org/\">Enlightenment</a> - Window manager bundled with a whole suite of libraries to help you create beautiful user interfaces.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.fluxbox.org/\">Fluxbox</a> - Window manager for X, lightweight and easy to handle but full of features to make an easy and fast desktop experience. Built using C++.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://fvwm.org/\">FVWM</a> - ICCCM-compliant multiple virtual desktop window manager for X. Extremely powerful.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://i3wm.org/\">i3</a> - Tiling window manager. BSD-licensed. Primarily targeted at advanced users and developers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.joewing.net/projects/jwm/\">JWM</a> - Lightweight window manager for X11. Good choice for older and/or less powerful systems, though perfectly capable of running on modern systems. Built using C.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.nongnu.org/ratpoison/\">ratpoison</a> - A simple window manager with no library dependencies, no graphics, and no decorations. Modeled after GNU Screen.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://sawfish.tuxfamily.org/\">Sawfish</a> - Extensible window manager. Its aim is to manage windows in the most flexible and attractive manner possible. Built using Lisp-based scripting language.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/wmii/\">wmii</a> - Small, scriptable window manager, with a 9P filesystem interface and an acme-like layout.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>X Windows Managers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://xmonad.org/\">xmonad</a> - Dynamically tiling X11 window manager. Makes work easier by automating aligning and searching for windows. Built using Haskell.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-09T14:11:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2><h3>Bash Learning Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://linux.die.net/Bash-Beginners-Guide/\">Bash Guide for Beginners</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-04T16:19:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2><h3>Bash Learning Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://linux.die.net/abs-guide/\">Advanced Bash-Scripting Guide</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-04T16:19:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2><h3>Bash Learning Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/a_z_e_t/inpresentation\">Beautiful Bash: Let's make reading and writing bash scripts fun again!</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-13T16:57:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2><h3>Bash Learning Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://kvz.io/blog/2013/11/21/bash-best-practices/\">Best Practices for Writing Bash Scripts</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-13T16:57:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2><h3>Bash Learning Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://google.github.io/styleguide/shell.xml\">Shell Style Guide</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-13T16:57:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2><h3>Bash Learning Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a hre